					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This damaged and undated inscription belongs to the reign of the king <hi rend="bold">Vikramāditya-Bhaṭāra</hi> and mentions <hi rend="bold">Ayyāvoḷe</hi> (i.e., the modern Aihoḷe). The writer was Chandradēva. In the absence of the date it is not possible to assign the epigraph definitely to Vikramāditya I or Vikramāditya II. Probably it belongs to the latter. </p>						

						</summary>
